A man in connection with the murder of Stellenbosch University student Robyn Pearce will appear in the Cape Town Magistrate s Court on Monday.The body of 20-year-old Maties student was discovered in an apartment block on 2 December with multiple stab wounds.The suspect, 27, was arrested in his home in Ottery on Wednesday and it is believed he had been working at the apartment block.According to reports the suspect was a construction worker at the Beach Court apartment building in Sea Point where Pearce s body was found.When the incident occurred construction and repair work were being carried out on the building.SAPS spokesperson Andre Traut confirmed that the suspect is due to make a court appearance in the Cape Town Magistrate court on Monday for murder chargers.Pearce was buried in Durban on Saturday.-TNA Reporter